Step_Project_2 😊

Welcome to the Step_Project_2 repository! 🎉 This is a Node.js application with Docker support and integrated into a Jenkins pipeline for
Continuous Integration and Continuous Deployment (CI/CD). Below you'll find an overview of the project structure and how to get started. 
Additionally, this project is part of a larger system, as described in ---> https://github.com/sashaloven/dan_it_homework/tree/main/Projects/Step_project_3 😎

Prerequisites 🛠️

Before using this repository, make sure you have the following:
- Docker 🐳 installed and running on your system to build and run the containerized application.
- Node.js 🚀 installed for local testing (though Docker will take care of dependencies in the container).
- Jenkins 🔧 configured for CI/CD with access to this repository.

Setting Up Locally 💻

1. Clone the repository
Clone this repository to your local machine using Git:

> git clone <repository-url>
> cd Step_Project_2

2. Install dependencies
If you want to run the application locally, first install the dependencies:

> npm install

3. Running the app
You can start the app locally with:

> node index.js
The application should now be running on the default port (or the one specified in the code). 🎉

Running the Application with Docker 🐳
The repository includes a Dockerfile to containerize the application. To build and run it using Docker:

1. Build the Docker image:

> docker build -t step-project-2 .

2. Run the Docker container:

> docker run -p 3000:3000 step-project-2

The application will be available at http://localhost:3000. 🎈

Running Tests 🧪
Unit tests for the application are located in the test/app.test.js file. To run the tests:

> npm test

Jest (or the testing framework defined in package.json) will run the tests and show the results in your terminal. ✅


